<subSubSection pageNumber="290" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">Note:</emphasis>
A later homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">A. barbatus</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
and hence illegitimate. Although Fosberg (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">Taxon</emphasis>
25: 325. 1976) argued that 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1771)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">A. barbatus</emphasis>
L. (1771)
</taxonomicName>
is merely a modification of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">A. barbatus</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
, it seems clear that this is not the case. In 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">Syst. Nat.</emphasis>
, ed. 13: 759. 1774, both this and the species described in 1759 (though named as 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1763)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1763" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Andropogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="polydactylos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">A. polydactylos</emphasis>
L. (1763)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="290">nom. illeg.)</emphasis>
were recognised.
</paragraph>
